 <h3 class="title"><a href="node/1611#comment-19550" class="active">Some links</a></h3>
 <div class="content"><p >See <a href="http://lambda-the-ultimate.org/classic/message9112.html">A Revolution in Logic?</a> for a discussion on IF, and <a href="http://lambda-the-ultimate.org/node/204">Introduction to computability logic</a> for an introduction to another project that builds logic of computation.</p>
<p >[on edit: note that IF paper suggests a way of living with G&ouml;del's first incompleteness<br >
theorem, thus winning my simpathy for IF itself and any adopters of it]</p></div>
 <div class="links">By <a href="user/1071" title="View user profile.">Andris Birkmanis</a> at Mon, 07/10/2006 - 17:39 | <a href="user/login">login</a> or <a href="user/register">register</a> to post comments</div>
